    • uploadCSV

      public UploadHistoryquotesSuccess uploadCSV(Integer idGtNetSecurityImpHead, org.springframework.web.multipart.MultipartFile[] uploadFiles, Integer idTenant) throws Exception
      Uploads and processes a CSV file containing GTNet security import positions.

      The CSV file must have a header row with column names that map to entity fields:

      • isin - International Securities Identification Number
      • tickerSymbol (or ticker_symbol, ticker) - Stock ticker symbol
      • currency - ISO 4217 currency code (required)

      Processing rules:

      • At least ISIN or tickerSymbol must be provided for each row
      • Currency is always required
      • Duplicate entries (same ISIN + currency) already in the database are skipped
      • Duplicate entries within the file are skipped
      • All string values are converted to uppercase
      Specified by:
      uploadCSV in interface GTNetSecurityImpPosJpaRepositoryCustom
      Parameters:
      idGtNetSecurityImpHead - the header ID to associate positions with
      uploadFiles - array of uploaded CSV files (only first file is processed)
      idTenant - the tenant ID for access verification
      Returns:
      upload result statistics
      Throws:
      SecurityException - if tenant doesn't have access to the header
      Exception - if file processing fails

    • deleteLinkedSecurity

      public GTNetSecurityImpPos deleteLinkedSecurity(Integer idGtNetSecurityImpPos, Integer idTenant)
      Description copied from interface: GTNetSecurityImpPosJpaRepositoryCustom
      Deletes the linked security from a position and removes it from the system. The position itself remains and can be queried again via GTNet.

      This operation:

      1. Unlinks the security from the position (sets security reference to null)
      2. Deletes all history quotes for the security
      3. Deletes the security entity from the database
      Specified by:
      deleteLinkedSecurity in interface GTNetSecurityImpPosJpaRepositoryCustom
      Parameters:
      idGtNetSecurityImpPos - the position ID
      idTenant - the tenant ID for access verification
      Returns:
      the updated position with security set to null

    • createFromImportTransactionHead

      public GTNetSecurityImpHead createFromImportTransactionHead(Integer idTransactionHead, Integer idGtNetSecurityImpHead, String headName, Integer idTenant)
      Description copied from interface: GTNetSecurityImpPosJpaRepositoryCustom
      Creates GTNet security import positions from an import transaction head. Reads ImportTransactionPos entries where security is null and (isin or symbolImp exists), then creates corresponding GTNetSecurityImpPos entries. Can create a new header or add to an existing one. Skips duplicates (same ISIN + currency) and entries with invalid data.
      Specified by:
      createFromImportTransactionHead in interface GTNetSecurityImpPosJpaRepositoryCustom
      Parameters:
      idTransactionHead - the import transaction head ID to read positions from
      idGtNetSecurityImpHead - optional existing header ID to add positions to (null to create new)
      headName - name for new header (required if idGtNetSecurityImpHead is null)
      idTenant - the tenant ID for access verification
      Returns:
      the GTNet security import header (existing or newly created)
